```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false;
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

Explanation: 
The idea is to calculate the logarithm base 3 of the given number `n`. If `n` is a power of three, then the logarithm will be an integer. We use the `% 1 == 0` check to ensure the result is an integer, not a decimal. If it's an integer, we return `true`, otherwise, we return `false`.

Note: This solution works because `log(a^b) = b * log(a)`, so `log(n) / log(3)` is equivalent to `x` in `n = 3^x`. If `x` is an integer, `log(n) / log(3)` will be an integer as well. If `x` is not an integer, `log(n) / log(3)` will be a decimal.

